additional_house_rules:
Please be aware, you must show government issued ID, which will be photographed, before you can receive keys.

 If you are checking in using our lockbox system, you must send a picture of your ID to my assistant before you receive the lockbox codes.

 Failure to do so will result in a cancellation of reservation and NO REFUND will be given. No exeptions!!!

Please keep the place clean. You must tidy up before checkout. That includes taking out the trash. 

No smoking in the unit, or anywhere on the property! 

Please DO NOT invite guests (who are not part of the reservation) to spend the night. 

When you check out please throw used towels and sheets in a corner of the rooms. Do not make the beds! 

Do not re arrange the furniture in any way or for any reason. Do not dismantle any device or devices in the unit. 

Do not keep the lights on when you go out. 

Do not leave AC unit on when you are not home.

Keep loud noises to a minimum after 10pm on weekdays. 

When checking out please leave the keys in the lockbox or on the counter. Your choice. 

Take all your trash out with you at check out. Do Not leave trash in the unit. 

Pets must be pre-approved by me before your arrival date. There is a fee of 50.00. 

Thank you
description:
Large studio with 2 shared bathrooms available for rent on 119th St. 

The unit is fully furnished with a full sized bed, a sofa bed, table and chairs, a full fridge, microwave, and toaster.

It has beautiful hardwood floors and  exposed brick.

The unit is extremely large and is fully renovated. It's on the 3rd floor of a Brownstone. It has a modern design with a rustic feel that preserves the true essence of Harlem. 

This space is your dream accommodation to offset your dream vacation!!

Cable TV, Wifi, High Speed Internet, Coffee, Tea, Water

My assistant will come by to check you in, but you will be alone for your stay.

The neighborhood of central Harlem is very diverse and full of culture! 

We are a few blocks from Historic 125th Street and The Apollo Theatre! A few blocks from 8th avenue (Restaurant Row)!!!!

The 2,3 trains are a few blocks away for an easy commute anywhere in the city!

The ABCD on St. Nicholas Ave and  4,5,6 trains on Lexington Ave and 125th street are about 8 minutes  by walking

This is a prime location for transit! Everything is right there!!!!
